                    <msContents>
                        <summary>A woodblock printed astronomical study by the Qing-dynasty astronomer You Yi in Kanbun, with appendix in Kunten by Nishikawa Seikyū, published in 1730. This work was imported to Japan during the Edo period and introduced the notion of solar rather than lunar measurement of time well before Japan abandoned the solar calendar in 1872.</summary>

                        <textLang mainLang="ja" source="IANA">Japanese</textLang>

